Fix three clippy 1.95 lints in upstream runtime crate

Pre-existing upstream code in `crates/runtime/` triggers three clippy
lints introduced in Rust 1.95 / clippy 1.95. None of these were caused
by the hardening patches (0001–0003); they're upstream drift surfacing
when CI runs `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings`
against a recent toolchain.

Apply the literal fixes clippy suggests:

- `bash.rs:125` — uninlined_format_args: `format!("{}", now)` →
  `format!("{now}")`.
- `policy_engine.rs:5` — duration_suboptimal_units:
  `Duration::from_secs(60 * 60)` → `Duration::from_hours(1)`.
  (`from_hours` is const-stable as of Rust 1.94.)
- `sandbox.rs:301-302` — map_unwrap_or:
  `.map(|s| s.success()).unwrap_or(false)` → `.is_ok_and(|s| s.success())`.

Once these are clear, clippy will continue into `tools/`, `commands/`,
and `rusty-claude-cli/` and may surface further upstream drift —
iterate the same way, or relax `-D warnings` for the eval phase.
---
diff --git a/rust/crates/runtime/src/bash.rs b/rust/crates/runtime/src/bash.rs
--- a/rust/crates/runtime/src/bash.rs
+++ b/rust/crates/runtime/src/bash.rs
@@ -122,7 +122,7 @@
             actor: get_git_actor().unwrap_or_else(|| "unknown".to_string()),
             pr_number: None,
         };
-        let _event = LaneEvent::ship_prepared(format!("{}", now), &provenance);
+        let _event = LaneEvent::ship_prepared(format!("{now}"), &provenance);
         // Log to stderr as interim routing before event stream integration
         eprintln!(
             "[ship.prepared] branch={} -> main, commits={}, actor={}",
